contentrichtext.text: In [[telecommunication]]s, '''proceed-to-select''' is a [[Signalling (telecommunication)|signal]] or event in the [[call-access phase]] of a [[data call]], which signal or event confirms the reception of a call-request signal and advises the calling data [[terminal equipment]] to proceed with the [[transmission (telecommunications)|transmission]] of the selection signals. Examples of proceed-to-select pertain to a [[dial tone]] in a [[telephone]] system. ==References== {{FS1037C}} [[Category:Telephony signals]] {{telecomm-stub}}
